org.ftcbootstrap.demos.navbot.opmodes

Class ResQBeaconTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • LinearOpMode
      • org.ftcbootstrap.ActiveOpMode
        • org.ftcbootstrap.demos.navbot.opmodes.ResQBeaconTest

  • public class ResQBeaconTest
extends ActiveOpMode
    Note: This Exercise assumes that you have used your Robot Controller App to "scan" your hardware and saved the configuration named: "Pushbot" and creating a class by the same name: PushBot.

    Note: It is assumed that the proper registry is used for this set of demos. To confirm please search for "Enter your custom registry here" in FtcRobotControllerActivity

    Summary: The ODS and MR Color Sensor mounted in between the Pushbot's claws. The program will use a combination of driving with encoders and driving with the ODS to reach the ResQ Beacon. The claws are used to indicate whether the color is red ( left claw) or blue ( right claw)

    See:

    org.ftcbootstrap.components,

    org.ftcbootstrap.components.operations.servos,

    org.ftcbootstrap.components.operations.motors

    Also see: PushBot for the saved configuration
